JOHANNESBURG - Bail has again been denied for international artist Zwelethu Mthethwa, who murdered sex worker Nokuphila Kumalo in 2013. His bail was immediately revoked after his conviction on 16 March.READ: Sex workers celebrate conviction of artist-murderer MthethwaHis defence again applied for bail this week, claiming Mthethwa needed to get his personal affairs in order. But Judge Patricia Goliath said on Friday that no preferential treatment would be afforded to the artist.His sentencing hearing will commence next montheNCA